positions.title: Lieutenant, Pharmacist Officer

positions.description:
-Contract Support Pharmacist serves as a member of the Purchased Operations Branch within the Pharmacy Operations Division (POD)
-Provides clinical expertise and clinical surveillance of the $7.1 billion TRICARE pharmacy contract working closely with clinical Contracting Officer Representative
-Coordinates with the pharmacy contractor to ensure that clinical formulary decisions made during the quarterly DoD Pharmacy and Therapeutics (P&T) Committee meeting are interpreted and implemented correctly
-Develops communication plans to notify beneficiaries of changes to their pharmacy benefit in a timely manner
-Resolves complaints and issues with performance of pharmacy care delivery issues and other contractual requirements by directly responding to beneficiaries and congressional inquiries
